### getRelocationEntry() {#abaf648d88dc891045a7cd0e989789370}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>RelocationEntry llvm::RuntimeDyldMachO::getRelocationEntry (unsigned SectionID, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/objectfile">ObjectFile</a> &amp; BaseTObj, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/object/#acc360db994cbcc482937196bf406df98">relocation&#95;iterator</a> &amp; RI) const</>}
  labels = {["inline", "protected"]}>
Given a <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/object/#acc360db994cbcc482937196bf406df98">relocation&#95;iterator</a> for a non-scattered relocation, construct a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/relocationentry">RelocationEntry</a> and fill in the common fields.

The &#39;Addend&#39; field is <em>not</em> filled in, since immediate encodings are highly target/opcode specific. For targets/opcodes with simple, contiguous immediates (e.g. <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/x86">X86</a>) the memcpyAddend method can be used to read the immediate.

</MemberDefinition>

### getRelocationValueRef() {#ac01d9cc5d2d4a3b6662c7096e54bf8ad}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; RelocationValueRef &gt; llvm::RuntimeDyldMachO::getRelocationValueRef (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/objectfile">ObjectFile</a> &amp; BaseTObj, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/object/#acc360db994cbcc482937196bf406df98">relocation&#95;iterator</a> &amp; RI, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/relocationentry">RelocationEntry</a> &amp; RE, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/runtimedyldimpl/#a22b1a24bb422a0f0896dd84dff7933e2">ObjSectionToIDMap</a> &amp; ObjSectionToID)</>}
  labels = {["protected"]}>
Construct a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/relocationvalueref">RelocationValueRef</a> representing the relocation target.

For Symbols in known sections, this will return a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/relocationvalueref">RelocationValueRef</a> representing a (SectionID, Offset) pair. For Symbols whose section is not known, this will return a (SymbolName, Offset) pair, where the Offset is taken from the instruction immediate (held in RE.Addend). In both cases the Addend field is <em>NOT</em> fixed up to be PC-relative. That should be done by the caller where appropriate by calling makePCRel on the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/relocationvalueref">RelocationValueRef</a>.
